      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -2128,
        48
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "width": 820,
        "height": 720,
        "content": "## AI Code Review Assistant\n\nAutomatically analyzes GitHub pull requests and provides AI-powered suggestions for code improvements. Reviews code quality, security, performance, and best practices. Generates detailed review comments, identifies issues, and suggests fixes.\n\n## How it works\n\n1. **Trigger** — Watches for new pull requests or manual trigger\n2. **Fetch PR Details** — Retrieves PR metadata and changed files from GitHub\n3. **Analyze Code** — Extracts code diffs and sends to AI for review\n4. **Review & Score** — AI analyzes code quality, security, performance\n5. **Generate Suggestions** — Creates detailed review comments with fixes\n6. **Post Review** — Posts review comments back to GitHub PR\n7. **Log Results** — Stores review data for tracking and analytics\n\n## Setup steps\n\n1. **GitHub** — Add your GitHub token and repository details\n2. **OpenAI/Claude API** — Configure API key for code analysis\n3. **Webhook** — Enable GitHub webhook for PR events\n4. **PostgreSQL** — Create `code_reviews` table for storing results\n5. **Slack** — Add webhook URL for notifications (optional)\n6. **Test** — Run manually with a test PR to verify connections"
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
